                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./361:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-02T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 2, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Your 23, March 19, 6 p.m. The local representative of the Pan American
                    Airways now states that he hopes to be able to make some kind of a working
                    arrangement with the Government of Honduras shortly after adjournment of the
                    Congress April 10.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
